body:
This commit extends c36dd885 not to create a temporary wire for
expressions that are only used for assign op. This is safe because the
type of lhs should be expliclit.

```mlir
hw.module @NoExtraTemporaryWireForAssign(%a: i2) {
  %0 = hw.struct_create (%a) : !hw.struct<foo: i2>
  %1 = sv.wire : !hw.inout<struct<foo: i2>>
  sv.assign %1, %0 : !hw.struct<foo: i2>
  hw.output
}
```

Before:
```verilog
 wire struct packed {logic [1:0] foo; } _GEN;

 wire struct packed {logic [1:0] foo; } _GEN_0 = '{foo: a}; 
 assign _GEN = _GEN_0;
```
After:
```verilog
  wire struct packed {logic [1:0] foo; } _GEN; 

  assign _GEN = '{foo: a};  
```
